breaksSchedule - Variable in class com.anylogic.libraries.processmodeling.ResourcePool
 
breakTaskMayPreemptOtherTasks(T) - Method in class com.anylogic.libraries.processmodeling.ResourcePool
Sets whether 'End of shift' task may preempt the task currently being executed, if any.
In other words, 'true' means that unit will "drop its work" right at the moment of its shift end.
If 'false', then the unit will finish all its tasks with less priority.
Note that 'true' option has exceptions: current unit task may have a "non-interruptable" option NO_PREEMPTION.

'End of shift' task is the task for unit when its shift time ends.
breakTaskPreemptionPolicy(T) - Method in class com.anylogic.libraries.processmodeling.ResourcePool
Specifies the policy for 'End of shift' task preemption:
NO_PREEMPTION - cannot be preempted (unit will "take a rest" until its new shift begins)
TERMINATE - may be preempted and will be terminated (unit may be "woken up" during its off-shift time)

'End of shift' task is the task for unit when its shift time ends
breakTaskPriority(T) - Method in class com.anylogic.libraries.processmodeling.ResourcePool
Sets the priority of 'End of shift' task.

'End of shift' task is the task for unit when its shift time ends

resource usage statistics.

destroyExcessUnits - Variable in class com.anylogic.libraries.processmodeling.ResourcePool
[actual for capacity defined directly, by schedule or by on/off schedule]
If true, once the capacity of pool decreases, all the excess units will be destroyed (and removed from their population, if any), so for the next capacity recovery, brand new units will be created.
If false, units are retained alive when the capacity of pool decreases (this is like their shift ends) and reactivated when capacity recovers

endOfShiftTaskMayPreemptOtherTasks(T) - Method in class com.anylogic.libraries.processmodeling.ResourcePool
Sets whether 'End of shift' task may preempt the task currently being executed, if any.
In other words, 'true' means that unit will "drop its work" right at the moment of its shift end.
If 'false', then the unit will finish all its tasks with less priority.
Note that 'true' option has exceptions: current unit task may have a "non-interruptable" option NO_PREEMPTION.

'End of shift' task is the task for unit when its shift time ends.
endOfShiftTaskPreemptionPolicy(T) - Method in class com.anylogic.libraries.processmodeling.ResourcePool
Specifies the policy for 'End of shift' task preemption:
NO_PREEMPTION - cannot be preempted (unit will "take a rest" until its new shift begins)
TERMINATE - may be preempted and will be terminated (unit may be "woken up" during its off-shift time)

'End of shift' task is the task for unit when its shift time ends
endOfShiftTaskPriority(T) - Method in class com.anylogic.libraries.processmodeling.ResourcePool
Sets the priority of 'End of shift' task.

'End of shift' task is the task for unit when its shift time ends

extendDelay(Agent, double) - Method in class com.anylogic.libraries.processmodeling.Delay
Extends delay for the given agent ( it is possible to pass null as an argument - in this case all delayed agents will be affected ).
Note that this function has no effect for agents which have finished their delay and are currently waiting to be consumed by subsequent blocks (because of 'pull' protocol)

This function is available only for timeout type Delay blocks.

free(Agent) - Method in class com.anylogic.libraries.processmodeling.Wait
Tells the queue to release the given agent and forward it to the 'out' port.
Since this method is called, the agent may leave the Queue block via 'out' port, but it 'holds' the queue capacity until it is actually pulled from this queue block.
Moreover, if the Queue block has corresponding configuration, the given agent may be preempted or it may exit queue by timeout during waiting on 'out' port.
"On at exit" code is called for the given agent.
This method returns true if the agent has been succesfully released and false in case when there is no such agent in the queue or the given agent is already exiting queue due to timeout or preemption or this agent is already waiting on 'out' port.
freeAll() - Method in class com.anylogic.libraries.processmodeling.Wait
Tells the queue to release all the agents and forward it to the 'out' port.
This method returns true if any agent has been succesfully released and false in case when there is no agents in the queue or all of them are already exiting queue due to timeout or preemption or are already waiting on 'out' port.

maintenanceTaskMayPreemptOtherTasks(T) - Method in class com.anylogic.libraries.processmodeling.ResourcePool
Sets whether 'End of shift' task may preempt the task currently being executed, if any.
In other words, 'true' means that unit will "drop its work" right at the moment of its shift end.
If 'false', then the unit will finish all its tasks with less priority.
Note that 'true' option has exceptions: current unit task may have a "non-interruptable" option NO_PREEMPTION.

'End of shift' task is the task for unit when its shift time ends.
maintenanceTaskPriority(T) - Method in class com.anylogic.libraries.processmodeling.ResourcePool
Sets the priority of 'End of shift' task.

'End of shift' task is the task for unit when its shift time ends

onCancelEnter(T, boolean) - Method in class com.anylogic.libraries.processmodeling.InputBlock
Callback executed when some agent currently living in preceding block decides not to go through this port.
onCancelExit(T, boolean) - Method in class com.anylogic.libraries.processmodeling.OutputBlock
This callback is executed when this (or some preceding) block decides to cancel the agent notification on 'At Exit'.
Cancelling is performed in backwards order.

This is done e.g. when agent is suspended.

onCancelExit(T, boolean) - Method in class com.anylogic.libraries.processmodeling.OutputBuffer
This callback is executed when this (or some preceding) block decides to cancel the agent notification on 'At Exit'.
Cancelling is performed in backwards order.

This is done e.g. when agent is suspended.

onUnitStateChange(T, boolean, ResourceTaskType, Agent, ResourceTask) - Method in class com.anylogic.libraries.processmodeling.ResourcePool
Code executed when new unit changes its activity.

Parameter:
T unit - resource unit.
boolean busy - true if the unit is busy (this doesn't mean that it was idle before), false if idle.
ResourceTaskType type - type of task, if unit is busy, one of: TASK_ENTITY, TASK_END_OF_SHIFT, TASK_WRAP_UP, TASK_BREAK, TASK_REPAIR, TASK_MAINTENANCE, TASK_CUSTOM constants from ResourceTaskType option list.
Agent agent - agent associated with this unit's task.

preemptionPolicy(T) - Method in class com.anylogic.libraries.processmodeling.ResourceTask
Specifies the policy for 'End of shift' task preemption:
NO_PREEMPTION - cannot be preempted (unit will "take a rest" until its new shift begins)
TERMINATE - may be preempted and will be terminated (unit may be "woken up" during its off-shift time)

'End of shift' task is the task for unit when its shift time ends

release(T) - Method in class com.anylogic.libraries.processmodeling.Queue
Tells the queue to release the given agent and forward it to the 'out' port.
Since this method is called, the agent may leave the Queue block via 'out' port, but it 'holds' the queue capacity until it is actually pulled from this queue block.
Moreover, if the Queue block has corresponding configuration, the given agent may be preempted or it may exit queue by timeout during waiting on 'out' port.
"On at exit" code is called for the given agent.
This method returns true if the agent has been succesfully released and false in case when there is no such agent in the queue or the given agent is already exiting queue due to timeout or preemption or this agent is already waiting on 'out' port.

resume() - Method in class com.anylogic.libraries.processmodeling.Delay
Resumes previously suspended Delay (if was not suspended, throws error).
After this method is called, all timeouts of agents being delayed are resumed, thus their timeouts totally get increased by amount of time spent between suspend() and resume() calls.
Unblocks input port if there is a room for incoming agents.

suspendResume - Variable in class com.anylogic.libraries.processmodeling.Delay
 
suspendResumeEntities - Variable in class com.anylogic.libraries.processmodeling.Assembler
This parameter defines whether the agent whose task is suspended
should be automatically suspended in its current flowchart block
and automatically resumed at the time there are available resources.
Suspend occurs because of SEIZE_ANY_RESOURCE and WAIT_FOR_ORIGINAL_RESOURCE
preemption policy, when the resource unit owned by the agent gets grabbed by
another task with higher priority.

There are callbacks: "On task suspended", it is executed after auto-suspend,
and "On task resumed", it is executed before auto-resume
